{
  "stem": "11174.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He went over and he got himself some bread, put a little chicken fat on the bread, and he had some Shabbos leftover, a polke from the chicken, and he ate that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Fine.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We finished.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We went down.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "One guy says to us-- now he, he stayed in is house, right?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Says to us, look what rich people are.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Not only he ate bread with-- with chicken fat, but even a polke too with.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's mind-boggling.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was saying that how, how rich he considered-- this is so rich that he can't afford both, both those things.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is a little indication, a little to make you understand what the standard of living was.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It depends what you call large.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, we had two large cities in-- in one side and the other side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was Tarnow, which was, I would say, about, let's say in kilometers, let's say about 35, 40 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the other side of the town was Rzeszow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In Yiddish it was called Rayshe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was a little smaller town and this was a little closer, I would say about 35 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and this was also pretty large town, industrial town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "People from the small town that they need merchandise to sell for their stores went here or in Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they went mostly with wagons-- wagons, horse and wagons.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But when I was a little kid already they started to go buses, so there was buses going in each town so it was a little easier.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Every morning this was the, the, the, let's call the [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] happenings in town. 6 o'clock in the morning, those that wanted to live a little excitement got up when the bus left.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The two buses left and said goodbye to people.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
